\section{Introduction}

This example document is meant to showcase some functionality provided by LLM's
more advanced \verba{llm_htmlplus} extension package.

For instance, the output HTML highlights code like this:
\begin{verbatimcode}[python]
def my_test_function(a, b, c):
    try:
        return a.getvalue()
    return b + c
\end{verbatimcode}

You can also generate PDF output using the 'pdf' output format:
\begin{verbatimcode}
> llm -f pdf exampledoc.llm
\end{verbatimcode}
(Don't forget the command line argument \verbcode`-w llm_htmlplus` if you didn't
specify a \verbcode`llm: default_workflow:` in your document's front matter.)

